-- Flight Centre to buy travel firm for $135 million
-- 
-- Sun Nov 11, 2007 5:58pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/11/us-flightcentre-acquisition-idUSSYU00347420071111

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - Australian travel firm Flight Centre Ltd ( FLT.AX ) said on Monday it has agreed to buy U.S. travel retailer Liberty Travel for $135 million. 

 Flight Centre plans to raise A$100 million ($91 million) in an institutional share placement to part fund the acquisition, the company said in a statement. ($1=A$1.10) (Reporting by  Denny Thomas )